Hi  Nathalie.

The following code works for me on my Ubuntu Linux machine.
Try launching this code in your favorite IDE, setting the classpath
to the libaries bundeled in the heritrix-2.0.0 distribution.

You can access the Heritrix WebUI by accessing
http://localhost:8080 with your browser.

It seems to me as if it has to be new String[] {&quot;-a&quot;, &quot;password&quot;}
instead of new String[] {&quot;-a password&quot;} you are useing.

Hope this helps,
Christian


import org.archive.crawler.Heritrix;
public class Launcher {

    /**
     * @param args
     * @throws Exception
     */
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        String homeDir = System.getProperty(&quot;user.home&quot;);

        // path to the Heritrix WebUI for deployment
        String webuiPath = homeDir + &quot;/.m2/repository/&quot; +
                                     &quot;org/archive/heritrix/&quot; +
                                     &quot;webui/2.0.0/webui-2.0.0.war&quot;;

        Heritrix.main(
                new String[] {
                        &quot;-a&quot;, &quot;test&quot;, // the password for WebUI access
                        //&quot;-u&quot;, // decomment if WebUI should be used only
                        &quot;-w&quot;, webuiPath, // Path to the WAR file of 
Heritrix WebUI
                        &quot;-j&quot;, &quot;./jobs&quot; // sets the path to the jobs 
directory, default is ./jobs I think
                        }
                );
    }

}
